ministers have increased their support for a political agenda that aims to revive patriotic education, renationalize Yasukuni Shrine, and revise the constitution. The contested nature of this agenda is evident in the critical responses of religious leaders and public intellectuals, and in their efforts to preserve the postwar gains in democratic institutions and prevent the erosion of individual rights. This timely treatment critically engages the contemporary debates surrounding secularization in light of postwar developments in Japanese religions and sheds new light on the role religion continues to play in the public sphere.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aNationalismxReligious aspectsxShinto. 0aReligious fundamentalismzJapan. 0aShinto and politicszJapan. 7aRELIGION / Shintoism.2bisacsh1 aMcMullen, Matthew, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2021 Englishz978311075419308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2021z9783110753974oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Hawaii Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073968840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082489016240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824890162423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780824890162/original  a978-3-11-073968-8  University of Hawaii Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus 